{"lemma":"مُخاطِ","slug":"مُخاطِ","root":"م.خ.ط","root_slug":"م-خ-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/م-خ-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38298"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B7%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mucus","examples":[{"text":"مُخَاط أَنْف","english":"nasal mucus"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alternative form of مُخَيْطَا (muḵayṭā, “sebesten”)","tags":["alt-of","alternative"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Classical Syriac ܡܚܘܛܐ (məḥōṭā, “mucus”). Doublet of مُخَيْطَا (muḵayṭā, “sebesten”)."},"ipa":["/mu.xaːtˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38298","headword_ar":"مُخَاطٌ","root":"mxT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mucus; snivel; what flows from the nose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luEaAb","text_ar":"لُعَاب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the mouth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amoxiTapN","text_ar":"اَمْخِطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"only. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxaATu Al$~ayoTaAni","text_ar":"مُخَاطُ الشَّيْطَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxaATu Al$~amos","text_ar":"مُخَاطُ الشَّمْس"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luEaAbu Al$~amos","text_ar":"لُعَابُ الشَّمْس"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyqu Al$~amosi","text_ar":"رِيقُ الشَّمْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", all these appellations having been heard from the Arabs, (TA,) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fine filmy cobwebs called gossamer, which are occasionally seen in very hot and calm weather, when the sun is high, floating in the air, in stringy"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flaky forms;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what appears in the sun's rays to him who looks into the air in the time of vehement midday-heat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mxAT Al$yTAn","text_ar":"مخاط الشيطان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is explained by Z and IB as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what comes forth from the mouth of the spider."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xyT","text_ar":"خيط"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}